Two items in one gofmt alignment section, each with a genuinely multi-line
element that paren-wraps. Elements no longer paren-wrap merely for being on a
wide line (see internal/printer's breakWideLiterals wiring), so this case uses
elements that are themselves multi-line to keep exercising the paren shape.

Re-formatting fmt's own output must not drift: the decorative paren puts the
element alone on its line, the shape that historically (#62) made `page` gain
a stray alignment cell on re-format, growing wider on every run.
goexprshape.Sanitize's before-hole collapse (guarded directly by
TestSanitizeBeforeCollapseIsParenOnly in internal/goexprshape/shape_test.go) is
still the fix for that. This case's own idempotence check no longer isolates
that one mechanism, though: internal/printer's fmtGoExprParts now runs
breakWideLiterals ahead of its final format.Source call, and breakWideLiterals
itself opens with a format.Source pass — so every reformat already goes through
gofmt twice, and the second pass re-parses text with no embedded newline left
near the hole to mis-align on, self-healing the single-pass artifact regardless
of the before-collapse. Verified by temporarily forcing Sanitize's inParens
condition to false: internal/goexprshape's own unit tests fail immediately, but
this corpus case keeps passing either way. The case is kept anyway — it still
pins that a genuinely multi-line, paren-wrapped, two-item literal formats and
reformats without drifting — just not as a discriminator for the historical
mechanism specifically.

-- input.gsx --
package ui

var nav = []item{
	{label: "Team View", icon: <UsersIcon>
		<title>users</title>
	</UsersIcon>, page: TeamViewPage{}, pathMatch: "/team"},
	{label: "Search", icon: <SearchIcon>
		<title>search</title>
	</SearchIcon>, page: ListPage{}, pathMatch: "/list/"},
}
-- fmt.golden --
package ui

var nav = []item{
	{label: "Team View", icon: (
		<UsersIcon>
			<title>users</title>
		</UsersIcon>
	), page: TeamViewPage{}, pathMatch: "/team"},
	{label: "Search", icon: (
		<SearchIcon>
			<title>search</title>
		</SearchIcon>
	), page: ListPage{}, pathMatch: "/list/"},
}
